#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:0.4"
msgid "Kosiyavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:0.5"
msgid "13. Dvebhāgasikkhāpada"
msgstr "13. The training rule on two parts"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np13.1, ms1V_2121
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpetun”ti, te thokaññeva odātaṃ ante ādiyitvā tatheva suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti."
msgstr "At that time, when the monks from the group of six knew that the Master had prohibited getting blankets made entirely of black wool, they added just a little bit of white on the edge. In this way they got blankets made entirely of black wool."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.3"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.4"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.5"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū thokaññeva odātaṃ ante ādiyitvā tatheva suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six act like this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2122
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.7"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, thokaññeva odātaṃ ante ādiyitvā tatheva suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.8"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.9"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.10"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, thokaññeva odātaṃ ante ādiyitvā tatheva suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you add just a little bit of white on the edge and in this way get blankets made entirely of black wool?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.11"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.12"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.12a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_2123
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.13"
msgid "“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārayamānena dve bhāgā suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ ādātabbā tatiyaṃ odātānaṃ catutthaṃ gocariyānaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk is getting a new blanket made, he should use two parts of entirely black wool, a third part of white, and a fourth part of brown."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.77
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:1.14"
msgid "Anādā ce bhikkhu dve bhāge suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ tatiyaṃ odātānaṃ catutthaṃ gocariyānaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he gets a new blanket made without using two parts of entirely black wool, a third part of white, and a fourth part of brown, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-np13.2, ms1V_2124
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.1"
msgid "Navaṃ nāma"
msgstr "New:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.2"
msgid "karaṇaṃ upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "newly made is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_2125
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.3"
msgid "Santhataṃ nāma"
msgstr "A blanket:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.4"
msgid "santharitvā kataṃ hoti avāyimaṃ."
msgstr "it is made by spreading out, not by weaving."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_2126
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.5"
msgid "Kārayamānenāti"
msgstr "Getting made:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.6"
msgid "karonto vā kārāpento vā."
msgstr "making or getting made."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2127
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.7"
msgid "Dve bhāgā suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ ādātabbāti"
msgstr "He should use two parts of entirely black wool:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.8"
msgid "dhārayitvā dve tulā ādātabbā."
msgstr "having weighed it, he should use two measures."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_2128
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.9"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ odātānanti"
msgstr "A third part of white:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.10"
msgid "tulaṃ odātānaṃ."
msgstr "one measure of white."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.11"
msgid "Catutthaṃ gocariyānanti"
msgstr "A fourth part of brown:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.12"
msgid "tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ."
msgstr "one measure of brown."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, pts-vp-pli3.227, ms1V_2130
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.13"
msgid "Anādā ce bhikkhu dve bhāge suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ tatiyaṃ odātānaṃ catutthaṃ gocariyānanti."
msgstr "Without using two parts of entirely black wool, a third part of white, and a fourth part of brown:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.14"
msgid "Anādiyitvā dve tule suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ tulaṃ odātānaṃ tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ karoti vā kārāpeti vā payoge dukkaṭaṃ,"
msgstr "for the act of making it, or getting it made, without using two measures of entirely black wool, one measure of white, and one measure of brown, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.15"
msgid "paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the blanket, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.16"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The blanket should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.17"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.18"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.19"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, santhataṃ anādiyitvā dve tule suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ tulaṃ odātānaṃ tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ kārāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this blanket which I got made without using two measures of entirely black wool, one measure of white, and one measure of brown, is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.20"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.21"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.22"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.23"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this blanket back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2131
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.24"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.25"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.26"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.27"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2132
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.28"
msgid "Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he makes one, or gets one made, for someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.29"
msgid "Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he obtains one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2133
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.30"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.31"
msgid "tulaṃ odātānaṃ tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ ādiyitvā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one using one measure of white and one measure of brown;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.78
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.32"
msgid "bahutaraṃ odātānaṃ bahutaraṃ gocariyānaṃ ādiyitvā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes on using more than one measure of white and more than one measure of brown;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.33"
msgid "suddhaṃ odātānaṃ suddhaṃ gocariyānaṃ ādiyitvā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one using just white and just brown;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.34"
msgid "vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a screen-wall, a mattress, or a pillow;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.35"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.36"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2134
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:2.37"
msgid "Dvebhāgasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The third rule, the training rule on two parts, is finished."
